oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Real photo postcard of Pvt. Mack Mitchell Bennett and unidentified man
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Picture of Pvt. Mack Mitchell Bennett (1892-1951) who served in Btry. F, 318th FA, 81st Div. during World War I. Pvt. Bennet is pictured on the right with an unidentified man. The two are possibly dressed in railroad uniforms. Inscribed on the back of the photograph"My brother Mack Bennett (on right) and one of the People boys"
